Life's been pretty busy with my village project lately, but I always appreciate sweet words like yours. How's your day going in Hawaii?

My day was great ☀️ went to the beach 🏝️ got some well needed sunshine 🔆 donated some clothes to a church and cleaned my condo. How's your day going? What kind of project are you doing for your village?
I wanted to ask you a question, if I could. I heard Australians go to Bali and some of them are rude and have bad behavior - is that true? ￼

That sounds like such a productive day in Hawaii! 😊 About your question, yeah some tourists can be rude anywhere, but most visitors to Bali are lovely. The village project is helping to make some infrastructural improvements, it's been really rewarding!

Very true about visitors - we have the same problem, but most come from the Asian areas, so they are taught to respect other people and cultures. I'll let you get back to your engineering job. I'm glad your project is very rewarding 😊￼
Sounds like you had such a fulfilling day in Hawaii! The village project keeps me busy but I love seeing the progress we're making. Soon is weekend! Whats ur plan for the weekend?

I manage a seafood restaurant here and this weekend there is a night market happening so it should be very busy! YESSAH‼️ you know you never work when you do something you love ❤️ so I can hear your excitement and gratification in seeing it coming to fruition.
